cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC 

This paper is related to natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with natural language processing. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as the task involves categorizing news headlines. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as the task involves using machine learning algorithms to classify the headlines. Finally, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of the algorithms used.
